Definition.WordDefinition: Biddy \Bid"dy\, n. [Etymology uncertain.] A name used in calling a hen or chicken. --Shak. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: Biddy \Bid"dy\, n. [A familiar form of Bridget.] An Irish serving woman or girl. [Colloq.] [1913 Webster]
biddy n 1: adult female chicken [syn: {hen}] 2: young bird especially of domestic fowl [syn: {chick}]
